http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Course-in-automobile-patient-assistance/article14000733.ece

The Palvancha-based Nava Bharat Vocational Institute will introduce two more vocational training courses – bedside patient assistant nursing course and two-wheeler and three-wheeler mechanism automobile course – soon. sAccording to a press release, the new courses will be offered in addition to the existing free vocational training programmes in as many as nine different trades at the Nava Bharat Ventures Limited’s vocational institute. The nursing course is meant for unemployed women with SSC qualification in the age group of 18-30 years. Unemployed men possessing SSC qualification in the age group of 18-30 years are eligible to apply for the automobile course. For further details, contact 8096999384.